               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="sa">Maṇimañjarī</title> is a 14<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>-century poem in eight chapters, attributed to <persName xml:lang="sa">Nārāyaṇapaṇḍitācārya</persName>. It is a <q>mythopoetic</q> history of the <term xml:lang="sa">Dvaita Vedānta</term> school of philosphy, beginning with the story of <term xml:lang="sa">Rāma</term> and <term xml:lang="sa">Kṛṣṇa</term>, continuing with the rise of Buddhism, <term xml:lang="sa">Advaita Vedānta</term>, and finally the birth of <persName xml:lang="sa">Madhvācārya</persName> (Sharma 1981, 219).</p></summary>
                  
